    "fresh": true,
    "content": "**AI & Robotics Snacks** — April 26, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 🧠 Mira Murati's New Lab Ordered the Premium GPU Buffet\n\nThinking Machines Lab has been secretive for months. Turns out the mystery product requires a frankly theatrical amount of compute.\n\n- **The cloud deal:** Mira Murati's startup signed a new single-digit-billion-dollar agreement with Google Cloud to expand training and deployment on NVIDIA GB300-based systems.\n- **Why it matters:** Google says the startup is among the first customers on its GB300 systems, which offer a 2x improvement in training and serving speed over the prior generation. The setup is specifically meant to support reinforcement learning workloads behind Tinker.\n\n*The lab raised $2 billion, stayed vague, and immediately went shopping for the expensive GPUs. Very subtle.*\n\n**Sources:** [TechCrunch](https://techcrunch.com/2026/04/22/exclusive-google-deepens-thinking-machines-lab-ties-with-new-multi-billion-dollar-deal/) | [NVIDIA and Google Cloud Collaborate to Advance Agentic and Physical AI](https://blogs.nvidia.com/blog/google-cloud-agentic-physical-ai-factories/)\n\n---\n\n## ☁️ NVIDIA and Google Cloud Are Building a Robot Gym the Size of a Small Country\n\nCloud infrastructure is now being marketed like a sovereign industrial policy with a side of humanoids. Which, to be fair, is where the money is.\n\n- **The scale:** NVIDIA and Google Cloud unveiled Vera Rubin-powered A5X instances that NVIDIA says can scale to 80,000 Rubin GPUs in one site and 960,000 across a multisite cluster, while promising up to 10x lower inference cost per token and 10x higher token throughput per megawatt.\n- **The physical AI pitch:** The same stack now bundles Gemini on Google Distributed Cloud with Blackwell GPUs, confidential G4 VMs, Isaac Sim, Omniverse libraries and Cosmos Reason 2 to train robots, digital twins and vision AI agents.\n\n*The cloud is now a factory. The factory is now a simulator. The simulator is now the product. Checks out.*\n\n**Sources:** [NVIDIA](https://blogs.nvidia.com/blog/google-cloud-agentic-physical-ai-factories/) | [NVIDIA and Partners Showcase the Future of AI-Driven Manufacturing at Hannover Messe 2026](https://blogs.nvidia.com/blog/ai-manufacturing-hannover-messe/)\n\n---\n\n## 🔓 Anthropic's Elite Cyber Model Escaped the Velvet Rope\n\nAnthropic said Mythos was too spicy for general release. A small unauthorized group reportedly took that as a product demo invitation.\n\n- **The breach:** Reuters reported on April 21 that unauthorized users gained access to Claude Mythos Preview through a third-party vendor environment, with the group reportedly using the model regularly after access was obtained.\n- **Why everyone is twitchy:** Mythos was launched under Project Glasswing for a limited set of defensive cybersecurity users because Anthropic says the model can identify serious software vulnerabilities and could be misused if it spreads.\n\n*Nothing says \"controlled rollout\" like a third-party environment doing improv security theater.*\n\n**Sources:** [Reuters via WHBL](https://whbl.com/2026/04/21/anthropics-mythos-model-accessed-by-unauthorized-users-bloomberg-news-reports/) | [TechCrunch](https://tech.yahoo.com/cybersecurity/articles/unauthorized-group-gained-access-anthropic-232645264.html)\n\n---\n\n## 🧬 OpenAI Is Offering $25,000 for a Bio Jailbreak\n\nOpenAI released GPT-5.5 and immediately followed it with: please try to break the biology safeguards, but professionally.\n\n- **The challenge:** OpenAI launched a GPT-5.5 Bio Bug Bounty on April 23, offering $25,000 for the first universal jailbreak that defeats its five-question bio safety challenge.\n- **The scope:** The program is limited to GPT-5.5 in Codex Desktop, with applications open through June 22, testing scheduled from April 28 to July 27, and all findings covered by NDA.\n\n*Frontier model launches now come with benchmarks, pricing, and a cash prize for anyone who can make safety have a very bad day.*\n\n**Sources:** [OpenAI](https://openai.com/index/gpt-5-5-bio-bug-bounty/) | [GPT-5.5 System Card](https://openai.com/index/gpt-5-5-system-card/)"
  }
